  <summary>2/4/1997--Introduced.
Amends the Internal Revenue Code to provide a special rule for a person whose parent is deceased for purposes of the generation-skipping transfer tax. Makes such rule inapplicable to an individual who is not a lineal descendant if there is a living lineal descendant.</summary>
